work.work-title: B R A I N S T A V E S

credit.credit-words: B R A I N S T A V E S

direction-type.words: Annoyed; angry, but under your breath (leggiero e non legato), but gradually feeling better
Drunk; lean into the glissandi (and lean for real); poco a poco cresc.
Like an echo in an empty train station, but the train is coming
Still lyrical, but with the wide-eyed wonder of having just discovered the top of your head
